com.w2.api.engine.events.gesture

Class GestureEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.w2.api.engine.events.gesture.GestureEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RobotEvent, W2Event

    public class GestureEvent
extends java.lang.Object
implements RobotEvent
    A 'Robot' can be subscribed to a 'GestureEvent'

    Because a registered `GestureEvent` is evaluated on every arrival of `RobotSensorSet` data for `Robot`, Wonder Workshop recommends that the shouldAlertHandler execution code should be relatively lightweight and non-blocking to prevent performance degradation.

    When a 'GestureEvent' happens on a 'Robot', the 'GestureEvent' is posted to the Robot Event Bus. (See EventBusFactory.getRobotEventBus(int))

      • setEventPhaseMask

        public void setEventPhaseMask(int eventPhaseMask)
        Tells the `GestureEvent` to trigger when it enters specific `EventPhase` phases.
        Certain events recognize phases in the event, and can be configured to trigger upon entry into any of these phases.

        As of this writing, these events are `gestureSlideAlongAxis` and `gestureDrop`.
        - EventPhase.IDLE
        Nothing is happening; waiting for event to start.
        - EventPhase.STARTED
        The gesture might be starting. but it might be some other gesture.
        - EventPhase.ESTABLISHED
        The gesture has definitely started.
        - EventPhase.COMPLETED
        The gesture has finished.
        - EventPhase.CANCELLED
        The gesture started, but it was a false positive (it wasn't this gesture after all).
        Parameters:
        eventPhaseMask - Bitwise-OR of `WWEventPhase` enums.
